      "writtenOn": "2017-09-23T01:23:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t like duplication of this code (here and in downloadSwarmingBotCode).\n\nPlease rename \u0027configureLogging\u0027 into \u0027init\u0027 and move all initialization there.\n\nfunc (agent *Agent) init(ctx context.Context, serviceAccount string) (context.Context, error) {\n  ...\n\n  ctx \u003d teelogger.Use(ctx, config.NewLogger)\n\n  var err error\n  agent.hostname, err \u003d metadata.InstanceName()\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    return ctx, err\n  }\n  agent.server, err \u003d metadata.Get(\"instance/attributes/machine_provider_server\")\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    return ctx, err\n  }\n  agent.serviceAccount, err \u003d metadata.Get(\"instance/attributes/machine_service_account\")\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    return ctx, err\n  }\n\n  options :\u003d auth.Options{\n    GCEAccountName:         agent.serviceAccount,\n    ServiceAccountJSONPath: auth.GCEServiceAccount,\n  }\n  agent.httpClient, err \u003d auth.NewAuthenticator(ctx, auth.SilentLogin, options).Client()\n  if err !\u003d nil {\n    return ctx, err\n  }\n  agent.mp, err \u003d getClient(...)\n  ...\n}\n\nThis will also allow to get rid of long argument lists in handle(...).\n\nAlso, strictly speaking, each new instance of auth.Authenticator does a bunch of calls to metadata server, so its better to share them if possible.",
